<p><b><a href="/wiki/Saint_Petersburg" title="Saint Petersburg">Saint Petersburg</a></b>, the second-largest city in Russia, is situated at the head of the <a href="/wiki/Gulf_of_Finland" title="Gulf of Finland">Gulf of Finland</a> on the <a href="/wiki/Baltic_Sea" title="Baltic Sea">Baltic Sea</a>. This photograph shows the eastern end of <a href="/wiki/Vasilyevsky_Island" title="Vasilyevsky Island">Vasilyevsky Island</a>, known as the spit, surrounded by the river <a href="/wiki/Neva" title="Neva">Neva</a>. The <a href="/wiki/Old_Saint_Petersburg_Stock_Exchange_and_Rostral_Columns" title="Old Saint Petersburg Stock Exchange and Rostral Columns">Old Saint Petersburg Stock Exchange and Rostral Columns</a>, built in the <a href="/wiki/Greek_Revival_architecture" title="Greek Revival architecture">Greek Revival style</a> in the first decade of the nineteenth century, are visible in the centre.
